l. There is ample material here for a two semester course in abstract algebra. The importance of proof is stressed and rigorous proofs of almost all results are given. But care has been taken to lead the reader through the proofs by gentle stages. There are nearly 400 problems, of varying degrees of difficulty, to test the reader's skill and progress. The book should be suitable for students in the third or fourth year of study at a North American university or in the second or third year at a university in Europe, and should ease the transition to (post)graduate studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aAlgebra, AbstractvTextbooks. 0aAlgebra, AbstractxTextbooks. 4aAbstract Algebra. 4aIntroduction. 4aUniversal Algebra. 7aMATHEMATICS / Algebra / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics 2015z9783110438765oZDB-23-DMA0 cEPUBz97831103856010 cprintz978311034086040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311034087740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110340877423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110340877.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MTPY  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2015  aZDB-23-DMAb2015